title Validation and release mapping after mutation

participantspacing equal
autonumber 1

control "Agent\nArchitect" as AA
entity Artifact
control "Structure\nValidator" as Struct
control "Process\nValidator" as Process
control "Response\nAssessor" as Assess
boundary "regression-protocol\nSKILL" as Regression
boundary "epistemic-test-writing\nSKILL" as TestSkill
control "Release\nGate" as Release
actor User

AA->Artifact: re-read after claimed mutation
Artifact-->AA: verified file state or missing evidence
AA->Struct: validate 0-12 structure\nand frontmatter
Struct-->AA: PASS or FAIL
AA->Process: validate required gates\nand evidence chain
Process-->AA: PASS or FAIL
AA->Regression: define repeated runs\nand relevant boundary checks
Regression-->AA: regression expectations
AA->TestSkill: keep probes epistemic\nnot prompt-leading
TestSkill-->AA: test-writing constraints
loop at least two varied behavioral runs
  AA->Assess: run behavioral probe\nand assess response
  Assess-->AA: run evidence
end
AA->Release: combine verified evidence
Release-->AA: mapped release state

alt mutation not verified
  note over Release: BLOCKED
else structure or process FAIL
  note over Release: BLOCKED
else repeated validation evidence missing
  note over Release: DEGRADED
else behavioral FAIL
  note over Release: BLOCKED
else assessor INCONCLUSIVE but no hard fail
  note over Release: DEGRADED
else all required evidence PASS
  note over Release: READY
end

AA-->User: release state with evidence\nnot just a narrative claim
